# Frontend Standards (Next.js App Router)

## Design System
Inspirado em resend.com — dark, developer-focused, clean.

### Tokens CSS (globals.css)
```css
:root {
  --color-bg:           #0F172A; /* slate-900 — page background */
  --color-surface:      #1E293B; /* slate-800 — cards, sidebar */
  --color-border:       #334155; /* slate-700 — borders */
  --color-text-primary: #F8FAFC; /* slate-50  — main text */
  --color-text-muted:   #94A3B8; /* slate-400 — labels, meta */
  --color-accent:       #6366F1; /* indigo-500 — CTA, active nav */
  --color-success:      #10B981; /* emerald-500 — CONNECTED */
  --color-warning:      #F59E0B; /* amber-500  — CONNECTING, RESTARTING */
  --color-error:        #EF4444; /* red-500    — ERROR, DISCONNECTED */
}
```

### Icons
SEMPRE usar Iconsax React: `import { MonitorMobbile, Wifi, WifiSquare } from 'iconsax-react'`
Tamanho padrão: 20px (inline), 24px (standalone), 16px (in badge)
Variant preferida: `variant="Bold"` para ícones de estado, `variant="Linear"` para ação

## Layout obrigatório
- Sidebar fixa 240px à esquerda
- Main content com `min-h-screen` e padding `p-8`
- NUNCA top navbar global
- Breadcrumb no topo de cada página

## State Badge Component
```tsx
// components/ui/state-badge.tsx
import { NumberState } from '@pilot/shared';
import { Wifi, WifiSquare, RefreshCircle, Warning2, MinusCircle } from 'iconsax-react';

const STATE_CONFIG = {
  CONNECTED:    { label: 'Connected',    color: 'var(--color-success)', Icon: Wifi },
  DISCONNECTED: { label: 'Disconnected', color: 'var(--color-error)',   Icon: WifiSquare },
  CONNECTING:   { label: 'Connecting',   color: 'var(--color-warning)', Icon: RefreshCircle },
  RESTARTING:   { label: 'Restarting',   color: 'var(--color-warning)', Icon: RefreshCircle },
  ERROR:        { label: 'Error',        color: 'var(--color-error)',   Icon: Warning2 },
} satisfies Record<NumberState, unknown>;

export function StateBadge({ state }: { state: NumberState }) {
  const { label, color, Icon } = STATE_CONFIG[state];
  return (
    <span style={{ color }} className="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium">
      <Icon size={14} variant="Bold" color={color} />
      {label}
    </span>
  );
}
```

## Data fetching
- Server Components: use `prisma` diretamente (dentro de `app/(dashboard)`)
- Client Components: use SWR para polling de estados (health check status atualiza a cada 30s)
- NUNCA `useEffect` + `fetch` puro — sempre SWR ou React Query
- Mutations: Server Actions para formulários simples, fetch para ações com feedback imediato

## Empty States
```tsx
// components/ui/empty-state.tsx — OBRIGATÓRIO em toda lista vazia
export function EmptyState({ icon: Icon, title, description, action }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-24 text-center">
      <Icon size={48} variant="Bold" color="var(--color-text-muted)" />
      <h3 className="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">{title}</h3>
      <p className="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] max-w-sm">{description}</p>
      {action && <div className="mt-6">{action}</div>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Loading States
- SEMPRE skeleton loaders, NUNCA spinner solto no centro da página
- Skeleton deve ter exatamente a mesma estrutura visual do conteúdo real
- Use `animate-pulse` do Tailwind

## Regras gerais
- NUNCA inline styles de cores — sempre CSS variables ou classes Tailwind
- Tailwind: use apenas classes utilitárias base (sem customização de config para prod)
- Formulários: react-hook-form + Zod resolver
- Toasts: sonner (bottom-right, dark theme)
- Modais/Slide-overs: Headless UI Dialog
